@N0300:  save the return address
@N0301: .print "draw_y_line y_len=%d, y_arg=%d", y_len, y_arg
@N0305:  initialize vector gen with the y-coord in ACC
@N0307:  shift from 0-15 axis to -8 to +7
@N0310:   +/- 1024 screen coords, multiply by 64 to get to bit 0
@N0311:  Draw a segment with x=ACC, length=32 in vert_line_seg
@N0314:  move up one segment
@N0317:  shorten the remaining length by 32
@N0321:  test to see if y_len remaining is less than 32
@N0323:  otherwise, go round again for the next segment
@N0324:  pick up remaining length in pixels
@N0325:  shift into to bits 8-13
@N0330:  initialize vector gen with the y-coord in ACC
@N0332:  shift from 0-15 axis to -8 to +7
@N0333:   +/- 1024 screen coords, multiply by 64 to get to bit 0
@N0334:  Draw a segment with x=ACC
@N0336:  =============================================================
@N0337:  save S; AC still = S
@N0340:  AC = S/2
@N0341:  AC = S/2 + 0.5
@N0342:  x0
@N0343:  --- Iteration 1 ---
@N0344:  BR = S / x  (AC = remainder, ignore)
@N0345:  AC = quotient from BR
@N0347:  AC = S/x + x
@N0350:  AC = (S/x + x) / 2
@N0352:  x1
@N0353:  --- Iteration 2 ---
@N0362:  x2
